to the editor your dec 5 editorial televising the highest court asserts that by agreeing to televise arguments the supreme court would only bolster the credibility and legitimacy of the institution in a day when courtroom television shows are joining soap operas as popular entertainment where marriage has become the stuff of game shows and every major national event has turned into a docudrama including our presidential election i find this hard to believe if anything televising the court would help undermine one of the few institutions that has not been cheapened by mass media once televised the justices would inevitably suffer the injustices of sound bites and consciously or unconsciously become vulnerable to popular opinion let us restrain ourselves for a change and keep our court an honorable one shane stansbury new york dec 6 2000 the writer is a law student

